                        <h1>Awards Categories</h1>                                  
                        <h2>Innovations 2009 Design and Engineering Awards Categories</h2>
<IMG height=150 src="/print/images/content/Innovations.jpg" width=100 align=right>Looking for specific product examples? <A href="/print/docs/2K9_Innovations_Guide2.pdf" target=_blank>Download the 2009 awards category guide.</A>
<P><STRONG>Audio Accessories<BR></STRONG>Products designed to enable, enhance, connect and/or maintain home audio systems and components.</P>
<P><STRONG>Audio Components<BR></STRONG>Products designed to deliver, control, store and/or manage audio content including records, tapes, disc-based audio, MP3 and hard drive storage.</P>
<P><STRONG>Computer Accessories</STRONG><BR>Products designed primarily around single use functionality to enable, enhance, connect, power and/or maintain desktop and/or portable computer systems. </P>
<P><STRONG>Computer Hardware</STRONG><BR>Includes all desktop and portable computer systems capable of accepting user input, storing and retrieving data, displaying or outputting a video signal and are capable of running application software. Does not include products whose primary purpose is making and receiving phone calls.</P>
<P><STRONG>Computer Peripherals</STRONG><BR>Products designed to connect to, and extend the functionality of desktop or portable computer systems. Examples include products&nbsp;that provide printing, network and user input and output display.</P>
<P><STRONG>Digital Imaging</STRONG><BR>Products designed to enhance the visual experience and/or allow the user to capture, store and edit still or movie video images.</P>
<P><STRONG>Eco-Design and Sustainable Technology</STRONG> <BR>Innovative features incorporated into consumer electronics products that make them safe for the environment and sustainable, efficient and clean energy use, manufacturing processes that reduce use of environmentally relevant substances (lead, mercury), durability/end-of-life (reuse, refurbish, remanufacture, recycle), resource conservation, solar power, use of recylced inputs, untraditional forms of power and modes for providing technology/connectivity to developing communities.</P>
<P><STRONG>Electronic Gaming</STRONG><BR>Products designed to allow one or more users to interact with electronic games. Examples include consoles, controls, storage devices and network connectivity accessories.</P>
<P><STRONG>Enabling Technologies</STRONG><BR>Software embedded in silicon designed to provide functionality to finished products or subassemblies.</P>
<P><STRONG>Furniture</STRONG><BR>Items designed to facilitate the use of consumer electronics products and/or the collection and organization of individual components. The category also includes items designed to store, manage and/or display collections of recorded media.</P>
<P><STRONG>Headphones<BR></STRONG>Devices which allow users to listen to audio content (music, radio, video soundtracks, live TV broadcasts and telephone conversations). The devices may incorporate microphones for user voice response or input.</P>
<P><STRONG>Health and Wellness</STRONG><BR>Products designed to test, monitor, or analyze the health, well-being, fitness and/or medical condition of an individual or provide therapeutic benefit. Products should have significant electronic functionality as a central part of the itemâ€™s operation.</P>
<P><STRONG>High-Performance Audio</STRONG><BR>Separate audio components and speakers which provide for optimal performance and sound reproduction. Items are typically produced in very limited quantity and are handcrafted.</P>
<P><STRONG>Home Appliances</STRONG><BR>Products designed to provide home heating and cooling, food storage and preparation and home cleaning.</P>
<P><STRONG>Home Networking</STRONG><BR>Products and accessories which enable users to maintain a wired or wireless data network for the purpose of providing file, print and Internet access sharing. Systems may also include products and software which provide for remote and conditional access.</P>
<P><STRONG>Home Theater Speakers</STRONG><BR>Includes speakers whose primary purpose is incorporation into a home theater system.</P>
<P><STRONG>Home Theater Accessories</STRONG><BR>Items enable home theater component connectivity, power quality, mounting, storage and content management.</P>
<P><STRONG>In-Vehicle Accessories</STRONG><BR>Products designed to enable, enhance, connect and/or maintain in-vehicle audio, video, and navigation systems, and components.</P>
<P><STRONG>In-Vehicle Audio</STRONG><BR>Products and components designed to be part of an in-vehicle audio system.</P>
<P><STRONG>In-Vehicle Control/OEM Integration<BR></STRONG>Products and components designed to facilitate the integration of aftermarket and OEM audio, video, and navigation systems in vehicles.</P>
<P><STRONG>In-Vehicle Navigation/Telematics/ITS</STRONG><BR>Products and components designed to be part of an in-vehicle navigation and/or information retrieval and transmission service.</P>
<P><STRONG>In-Vehicle Video</STRONG><BR>Products and components designed to be part of an in-vehicle video system.</P>
<P><STRONG>Integrated Home Systems</STRONG> <BR>Products and components designed to be used as complete systems or subsystems in the home to control the distribution of and access to audio and video content. Systems also control lighting, energy and environmental systems and security access.</P>
<P><STRONG>Multi-Room Audio/Video<BR></STRONG>Systems specifically designed to allow users to centralize content and then redistribute via multiple simultaneous discrete streams to multiple locations in a home.</P>
<P><STRONG>Personal Electronics</STRONG><BR>Products designed around single function or multi-function uses which operate individually or in conjunction with other products.</P>
<P><STRONG>Portable Media Accessories</STRONG><BR>Products designed to enable, enhance, connect, carry and/or maintain portable media players.</P>
<P><STRONG>Portable Media Players<BR></STRONG>Products incorporating integrated storage and playback capability for audio and/or video content. Products have the capability to connect to desktop and portable computer systems to exchange content.</P>
<P><STRONG>Portable Power</STRONG><BR>Devices designed to facilitate the powering and/or charging of consumer electronic products. </P>
<P><STRONG>Telephones <BR></STRONG>Products designed to provide access to telephony services in the home and/or office.</P>
<P><STRONG>Video Accessories</STRONG><BR>Products designed to enable, enhance, connect and/or maintain home video systems and components.</P>
<P><STRONG>Video Components</STRONG><BR>Systems or components designed to provide for playback, storage and/or distribution of video signals and content in the home.</P>
<P><STRONG>Video Displays</STRONG><BR>Devices whose primary purpose is the display of video content not including items marketed and sold primarily as computer monitors.</P>
<P><STRONG>Wireless Handsets Accessories</STRONG><BR>Products designed to enable, enhance, connect, carry and/or maintain wireless handsets.</P>
<P><STRONG>Wireless Handsets</STRONG><BR>Items marketed primarily for the ability to provide wireless calling capability. The products in this category, in addition to having voice calling features, may also incorporate wireless data and Internet access features along with built-in camera and media playback functionality.<BR></P>
    
